<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06122</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROTECTING CONSUMERS AND MERCHANTS ENGAGED IN INTERNET TRANSACTIONS, CREATING FOR THIS PURPOSE THE ECOMMERCE BUREAU AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to create an environment founded on trust among consumers and merchants, as a means to increase the number of eCommerce participants, and ultimately achieve sustainable growth.

Aims to address the need to establish an eCommerce Bureau under the Dept. of Trade and Industry ( D T I ) that: 1) will be given the responsibility to carry out the provisions of this bill; 2) will ensure the implementation of the Electronic Commerce Act of 2000 (R.A.NO.8792); and will be the focal point in the monitoring and implementation of the Phil. eCommerce roadmap.

Proposes that the sale or exchange of digital products shall include the following:
internet retail of consumer goods; online travel services; digital media providers; ride hailing services for personal transport; and financial services offered through digital online platforms.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GATCHALIAN, WESLIE T.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-01-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Barba (000 2020-02-12)</td><td>2. Singson-Meehan (000 2020-06-11)</td><tr><td>3. Tan (A.S.) (000 2020-06-11)</td><td>4. Cueva (000 2020-06-24)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2020-02-05</td></tr></table>